primary_outcome.description:
1) Total retinal blood flow, as measured by Doppler OCT, will be correlated with visual acuity and the severity of PDR. This will be performed by the following analysis:
Pearson's correlation test of total retinal blood flow with logMAR (Logarithm of the Minimal Angle of Resolution) visual acuity before and after PRP;
Pearson's correlation test of total retinal blood flow with area of capillary drop-out on FA before and after PRP;
Pearson's correlation test of total retinal blood flow with areas of leakage on FA before and after PRP;
Pearson's correlation test of total retinal blood flow with areas of thickening on OCT before and after PRP.
Paired t test of total retinal blood flow on OCT before and after PRP.
